<body>
    <h1>Privacy Policy for Mindful Shopper Chrome Extension</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> [Date]
    </div>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Mindful Shopper ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about how we handle your data. This Privacy Policy explains how our Chrome extension collects, uses, stores, and protects your information when you use our service that helps you make mindful purchasing decisions through AI-generated guidance.</p>

    <h2>1. Data Collection Practices</h2>
    
    <h3>1.1 Information We Collect</h3>
    
    <p><strong>Product Information:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Product names, descriptions, and prices from e-commerce websites you visit</li>
        <li>Shopping cart contents and product URLs</li>
        <li>Website domain information where products are viewed</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>User Preferences:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Your mindfulness goals and shopping preferences (if provided)</li>
        <li>Extension settings and configuration choices</li>
        <li>Usage patterns within the extension</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Technical Data:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Extension version and performance data</li>
        <li>Error logs and diagnostic information (anonymized)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>API Usage Data:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Text prompts sent to OpenAI's API for generating mindful shopping guidance</li>
        <li>AI-generated responses received from OpenAI</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>1.2 How We Collect Data</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Automatically:</strong> When you browse e-commerce websites with our extension enabled</li>
        <li><strong>User Input:</strong> When you configure settings or provide preferences</li>
        <li><strong>API Interactions:</strong> When our extension processes product information through OpenAI's services</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Data Usage</h2>
    
    <h3>2.1 Primary Uses</h3>
    <p>We use your data exclusively to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Generate personalized AI-powered guidance to help you make mindful purchasing decisions</li>
        <li>Provide relevant "pep talks" when you attempt to add items to your cart</li>
        <li>Improve the accuracy and relevance of our mindfulness suggestions</li>
        <li>Maintain and improve extension functionality</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2.2 Data Processing</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Product information is processed in real-time to generate contextual advice</li>
        <li>No data is used for advertising, marketing, or commercial purposes beyond our core service</li>
        <li>Data is not sold, rented, or shared with third parties except as described in this policy</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
    
    <h3>3.1 Local Storage</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>User preferences and settings are stored locally using Chrome's storage API</li>
        <li>No sensitive personal information is permanently stored on your device</li>
        <li>Local data can be cleared by uninstalling the extension or clearing browser data</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.2 Data Retention</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Local Data:</strong> Retained until you uninstall the extension or clear browser storage</li>
        <li><strong>API Data:</strong> Product information sent to OpenAI is retained by OpenAI for up to 30 days as per their data retention policy</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> Anonymized usage data may be retained for up to 12 months for service improvement</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.3 Data Security</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>All data transmissions use HTTPS encryption</li>
        <li>API keys are stored securely and never exposed in client-side code</li>
        <li>Local data is protected by Chrome's built-in security measures</li>
        <li>We implement industry-standard security practices to protect your information</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    
    <h3>4.1 OpenAI API Integration</h3>
    
    <div class="highlight">
        <p><strong>Data Sharing:</strong> We share product information and user context with OpenAI to generate mindful shopping guidance.</p>
    </div>

    <p><strong>OpenAI's Data Handling:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>OpenAI retains API inputs and outputs for up to 30 days to provide services and detect abuse</li>
        <li>Data is then deleted unless legally required to be retained</li>
        <li>OpenAI does not use API data to train their models</li>
        <li>OpenAI's privacy practices are governed by their privacy policy: <a href="https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy">https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Data Transmitted to OpenAI:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Product names, descriptions, and prices</li>
        <li>Contextual information about your shopping session</li>
        <li>Your configured mindfulness goals (if provided)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4.2 No Other Third-Party Sharing</h3>
    <p>We do not share your data with any other third-party services, advertisers, or data brokers.</p>

    <h2>5. User Rights and Data Control</h2>
    
    <h3>5.1 Your Rights</h3>
    <p>Under applicable privacy laws (including GDPR and CCPA), you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request information about what data we have collected about you</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your data in a portable format</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Disable data collection by turning off the extension or uninstalling it</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.2 How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Disable Extension:</strong> Turn off the extension in Chrome's extension manager</li>
        <li><strong>Clear Local Data:</strong> Uninstall and reinstall the extension</li>
        <li><strong>Contact Us:</strong> Email us at [contact-email@example.com] for data requests</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-Out of AI Processing:</strong> Disable the extension's AI features in settings</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.3 California Residents (CCPA)</h3>
    <p>If you are a California resident, you have additional rights:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Right to know what personal information is collected and how it's used</li>
        <li>Right to delete personal information</li>
        <li>Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information (Note: We do not sell personal information)</li>
        <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising your privacy rights</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Compliance with Privacy Regulations</h2>
    
    <h3>6.1 GDPR Compliance</h3>
    <p>For users in the European Union:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> We process data based on legitimate interests (providing mindful shopping guidance)</li>
        <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Explicit consent is obtained for non-essential data processing</li>
        <li><strong>Data Protection Officer:</strong> Contact us for data protection inquiries</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>6.2 Data Transfers</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Data may be transferred to OpenAI's servers (located in the United States)</li>
        <li>Transfers are protected by appropriate safeguards and OpenAI's privacy commitments</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
    
    <h3>7.1 No Tracking Cookies</h3>
    <p>Our extension does not use tracking cookies or similar technologies for advertising or analytics purposes.</p>

    <h3>7.2 Functional Data Only</h3>
    <p>We only access website data necessary for our core functionality (product information on e-commerce sites).</p>

    <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our extension is not intended for use by children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>

    <h2>9. Data Breach Notification</h2>
    <p>In the unlikely event of a data breach that affects your personal information, we will:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Notify affected users within 72 hours of discovery</li>
        <li>Report the breach to relevant authorities as required by law</li>
        <li>Take immediate steps to secure the data and prevent further breaches</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>10. Policy Updates</h2>
    
    <h3>10.1 Notification of Changes</h3>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Changes in our data practices</li>
        <li>Updates to applicable laws</li>
        <li>Improvements to our service</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>10.2 How We Notify You</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Updated policies will be posted in the Chrome Web Store</li>
        <li>Significant changes will be communicated through the extension interface</li>
        <li>The "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy will be revised</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>10.3 Continued Use</h3>
    <p>Your continued use of the extension after policy updates constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.</p>

    <h2>11. Contact Information</h2>
    
